# Swift Package Manager
#
# NOTE: do NOT ignore `Packages/` — our local `Packages/WalletService` (the BDK seam) lives
# there and MUST be tracked. (The template line that ignored it was for SPM dependency
# checkouts, which live under .build/ anyway.) Package.resolved is COMMITTED on purpose:
# it pins exact dependency versions (CLAUDE.md §3 — BDK is pre-3.0; never float).
Package.pins
#*.xcodeproj

Carthage/Build/

# fastlane

**/fastlane/apikey.json
**/fastlane/report.xml
**/fastlane/README.md
**/fastlane/Preview.html
**/fastlane/test_output

# Firebase / FCM / push — NEVER commit (added preventively; see docs/notifications.md).
# Server-side SENDING keys (FCM service-account JSON, APNs .p8 — `*.p8` already ignored above) belong
# on the backend / in CI secrets, never in the repo or the app bundle. Firebase client-config files
# aren't needed by skip-notify, but ignore them too in case they ever get downloaded. The ONLY
# Firebase value that may live in the app is the non-secret numeric Sender ID.
google-services.json
GoogleService-Info.plist
**/firebase-service-account*.json
**/serviceAccountKey.json
**/*-firebase-adminsdk-*.json
